    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/21",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Also, make sure that the model possesses the basic properties that all derivatives models should possess, such as putâ€“call parity and other nonarbitrage conditions. Finally, the vetter should stress-test the model. The model can be stress-tested by looking at some limit scenario, in order to identify the range of parameter values for which the model provides accurate pricing. This is especially important for implementations that rely on numerical techniques.</p>",
      "page": 304,
      "polygon": [
        [
